    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1325571265,
    "creation_date" : 1325571265,
    "answer_id" : 8708593,
    "question_id" : 8708542,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Set.html#retainAll%28java.util.Collection%29\" rel=\"nofollow\">retainAll</a> method and get the intersection of your two sets.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1079173,
        "reputation" : 43706,
        "user_id" : 1076640,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/e0VNy.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "yshavit",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1076640/yshavit"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1325571469,
      "post_id" : 8708594,
      "comment_id" : 10837785,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "If the point of avoiding the iteration is for efficiency, <code>retainAll</code> probably won&#39;t help. Its implementation in <code>AbstractCollection</code> iterates."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 212481,
        "reputation" : 4215,
        "user_id" : 465323,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 94,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/48486463225c6705e51463adcafbb240?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Z&#233;ychin",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/465323/z%c3%a9ychin"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 2,
      "creation_date" : 1325572037,
      "post_id" : 8708594,
      "comment_id" : 10837887,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "yshavit is correct. Given that the O.P. is looking to see if <b>any</b> element exists in both sets, a proper algorithm would have an <code>O(1)</code> running time in the best case, whereas <code>retainAll</code> would have something along the lines of an <code>O(N)</code> (it would depend on the size of only 1 set) best-case running time."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 6301992,
        "reputation" : 337,
        "user_id" : 5626580,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-bWJFd_ZLRpU/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAY0/heI43UjgyuQ/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
        "display_name" : "Kir Kanos",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5626580/kir-kanos"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1695215692,
      "post_id" : 8708594,
      "comment_id" : 135994453,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "retainAll is destructive. It removes non common elements from the original List or Set. It gets an issue if you are in a loop and need to preserve the initial collection."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 26588,
      "reputation" : 11827,
      "user_id" : 69340,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 78,
