      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Be careful with equating &quot;not disjoint&quot; and &quot;contains any&quot;.  <code>setA.containsAll(setB)</code> returns <code>true</code> when <code>setB</code> is empty. So it reasons that <code>setA.containsAny(setB)</code> would also return <code>true</code>. However, <code>!Collections.disjoint(setA, setB)</code> returns <code>false</code>, as all sets are disjoint from the empty set."
