    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Wouldn't <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Collections.html#disjoint%28java.util.Collection,%20java.util.Collection%29\"><code>Collections.disjoint(A, B)</code></a> work? From the documentation:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Returns <code>true</code> if the two specified collections have no elements in common.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Thus, the method returns <code>false</code> if the collections contains any common elements.</p>\n"
