  "title" : "Something like &#39;contains any&#39; for Java set?",
  "body" : "<p>I have two sets, A and B, of the same type.</p>\n\n<p>I have to find if A contains any element from the set B.</p>\n\n<p>What would be the best way to do that without iterating over the sets?\nThe Set library has <code>contains(object)</code> and <code>containsAll(collection)</code>, but not <code>containsAny(collection)</code>.</p>\n"
